The stola had been the exclusive privilege of matronae since as early at least as the Second Punic War (Macrob. 1, 6, 13). It was not worn even by ingenuae if unmarried. The vitineas a distinctive portion ofa matrona’s costume are mentioned as early as Plaut. Milet Glor. 791.
